title: Single cell RNA-seq of CD1 mouse forebrain at embryonic day 15.5
abstract: Single cell RNA-seq was conducted on embryonic brains from wild-type CD1 mice at embryonic day 15.5 following The Illumina<c2><ae> Bio-Rad<c2><ae> SureCell Single-Cell RNA Sequencing workflow. Four cell captures and sequencing runs were conducted with four to eight fetal brains used for each collection. For each brain, the cerebral cortex was dissected and collected (although ventral forebrain structures, especially the gonglionic eminence may be mixed in due to difficulty in dissection).
overall_design: Single cell RNA-seq analysis of embryonic mouse cerebral cortex at E15.5
